JO  - AMJ
SP  - 369
EP  - 380
VL  - 30
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses statistical power with respect to contemporary management studies. A study is looked at which assesses statistical power in a population of management studies. The main codeterminants of statistical power are reviewed. The author notes three codeterminants of power: significance criterion, reliability of sample results, and effect size. Errors made by researchers with null hypotheses are mentioned. Small, medium, and large effect sizes are defined. Published research is referenced to discuss the implications of findings on statistical power.
AB  - The article discusses statistical power with respect to contemporary management studies. A study is looked at which assesses statistical power in a population of management studies. The main codeterminants of statistical power are reviewed. The author notes three codeterminants of power: significance criterion, reliability of sample results, and effect size. Errors made by researchers with null hypotheses are mentioned. Small, medium, and large effect sizes are defined. Published research is referenced to discuss the implications of findings on statistical power.
